            {
                "comment": "The class is fine, but it's set up so that if you're planning to be a horticulture major that can make very early lecture times you'll be ok.  If you have a secondary interest in horticulture (ie, this isn't your major) you're probably going to have a bad time.  To be fair, he's a cool dude (he's a potato wizard), but this class isn't perfect.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 2
            },
            {
                "comment": "Jiwan as a fantastic teacher.  He keeps everything very simple and REALLY, TRULY wants students to understand and learn the material.  There is no homework or papers and the grade is based on exams.  But he gives study aids and does a review before the exam.  The class was easy, but it was because of Prof Palta's great teaching style.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
